external_knowledge:
- "Top users by post count" refers to users who have the highest number of posts;
- "Comments" include both active and inactive comments;
- "Active comments" are comments where `is_active` is set to 1.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(followerID) AS accepted_followers_count
FROM followers
WHERE userID = 1 AND status = 'accepted';

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM comments
WHERE user_id IN (
  SELECT user_id
  FROM user_role_assignments
);

external_knowledge:
- "Public posts" are posts that are visible to everyone;
- "Private posts" are posts that are visible only to the user's followers;
- "Followers" are users who have accepted a follow request from another user.

- "gardeners" refers to users in the `users` table;
- "planted at least one flower" means the user has at least one post in the `posts` table;
- "bees" refers to likes in the `likes` table;
- "drawn to their blooms" means the total number of likes received by the user's posts.

- "storytellers" refers to users who have created posts;
- "tales" refers to the posts;
- "captured the hearts of at least two admirers" means the posts have been liked by at least two distinct users.

- "Gravitational pull of their posts" refers to the number of posts a user has made;
- "Number of stars that orbit them" refers to the number of accepted followers a user has;
- "Luminosity of the likes that shine upon their content" refers to the total number of active likes on their posts.

- "Indirectly followed" means being a follower of a follower, specifically at level 2 in the hierarchy;
- "Users with a specific role" refers to users who have role_id = 1;
- "Post count" refers to the number of public posts made by the users.

- "the gardener" refers to the user with `followerID` = 1;
- "the garden of accepted followers" refers to the set of users whose follow requests have been accepted by the gardener;
- "seeds" metaphorically represent the posts created by these accepted followers;
- "the first month of the year" refers to January 2023.

- "plants the most flowers" refers to the user who has the most posts;
- "waters them diligently" refers to the user who has the most engagement (likes and comments) with their posts;
- "enriches the soil with the most diverse nutrients" refers to the user who uses the most unique tags in their posts.

- "active engagement" refers to the sum of active likes and comments on users' posts;
- "top 5 users" means the users with the highest engagement scores;
- "likes and comments are the flowers blooming around their posts" is a metaphor for user interactions on posts.

- 'trees' metaphorically represent users in a social media context;
- 'leaves' represent posts made by users;
- 'gardeners' represent followers of users;
- 'accepted invitation' refers to the 'accepted' status in the followers table;
- 'no gardeners have shown interest' refers to the absence of a follower status (i.e., `f.status IS NULL`).

- "Photographers" refers to users who have posts tagged with 'photography';
- "Silent observers" refers to users who have their email notifications disabled;
- "Appreciated" means being followed by users with disabled email notifications.

- Engagement is calculated by the number of likes on a user's posts;
- The hierarchy of followers is used to understand the reach and influence of a user;
- The user with the highest total engagement is considered the most influential.
